    • requirement

      String requirement()
      Provides the specific requirement for this dialect.
      Returns:
      The version requirement for this dialect, or "none" if no requirement is required.

    • parseVersion

      default String parseVersion(String version)
      Used to parse version strings. Some dialects, such as Maria need their versions parsed because they format them in a specific manner.
      Parameters:
      version - The version to parse.
      Returns:
      The parsed version.

    • checkRequirement

      default boolean checkRequirement(String version)
      Used to check if the provided version meets the requirement we need.
      Parameters:
      version - The version to check.
      Returns:
      True if the provided version meets our requirement.
